Ecology. The new species occurs in seasonally astatic pools ( 30–190 m 2 in surface area, up to 40 cm deep). Associated fauna include amphibian larvae, cladocerans, copepods, ostracods, and a great diversity of aquatic insects (
Fischer et al . 2000
). Under natural conditions, at mean temperatures of 18 to 24°C, juveniles appear 2 days after innundation and mature individuals after 6 days.
